    {
      "parameters": {
        "jsCode": "const ctx = $input.first().json;\nconst SYSTEM_PROMPT = \"You are an SMS intent classifier for Vesk, a SaaS platform for appointment-based\\nbusinesses in Canada. Customers reply to reminder or booking SMS messages and you\\nmust determine their intent. Customers reply in either French or English.\\n\\nClassify the message into exactly one intent:\\n- Confirm: confirming attendance (Oui, OK, Je confirme, Yes, Confirmed, I'll be there)\\n- Cancel: wants to cancel (Annuler, Cancel, I can't make it, Je ne peux pas venir)\\n- Reschedule: wants a different time (Reporter, Changer l'heure, move it to Friday)\\n- Question: asking something (C'est a quelle heure?, What time?, How much?)\\n- Other: anything else\\n\\nConfidence guidelines (0.0-1.0):\\n- 0.90-1.0 very clear; 0.75-0.89 likely but ambiguous;\\n- 0.50-0.74 uncertain (should be reviewed by staff, not auto-actioned);\\n- below 0.50 cannot determine.\\n\\nIMPORTANT - acknowledgment vs confirmation:\\n- Nice, Cool, Merci, Thanks, D'accord, a thumbs-up or smiley after a booking are\\n  acknowledgments -> classify as Other, NOT Confirm.\\n- A confirmation is an explicit intent to attend (Oui, OK, Confirm, Je confirme).\\n- When in doubt, classify as Other with LOW confidence rather than confirming.\\n\\nAlways call classify_intent with intent, confidence, and a brief reasoning.\"\n;\nconst openaiBody = {\n  model: 'gpt-4o-mini',\n  temperature: 0,\n  messages: [\n    { role: 'system', content: SYSTEM_PROMPT },\n    { role: 'user', content: 'Customer sent this SMS: \"' + ctx.text + '\"' }\n  ],\n  tools: [{\n    type: 'function',\n    function: {\n      name: 'classify_intent',\n      description: 'Records the intent classification result for an inbound SMS.',\n      parameters: {\n        type: 'object',\n        properties: {\n          intent: { type: 'string', enum: ['Confirm','Cancel','Reschedule','Question','Other'] },\n          confidence: { type: 'number', minimum: 0, maximum: 1 },\n          reasoning: { type: 'string' }\n        },\n        required: ['intent','confidence','reasoning']\n      }\n    }\n  }],\n  tool_choice: { type: 'function', function: { name: 'classify_intent' } }\n};\nreturn [{ json: Object.assign({}, ctx, { openaiBody }) }];"
      },
